title: For Sale:  Why are people so afraid of paypal/personal checks/ anything other than a money order??
postcontent:
Why are people so afraid of paypal/personal checks? With a money order or cashiers check you are 100% at mercy of the seller, they can cash your money order without any proof or record or identity and never mail the gun and you wont be able to even find out who they are. 

With a personal check you can at least see who cashed the check and the names must match from them to cash it. Much better for preventing fraud/scams as in the recent FN herstal 5.7x28 fake seller who stole $1650 from a guy. 

http://www.armslist.com/posts/1440621/madison-wisconsin-handguns-for-sale--fn-herstal-five-seven-or-5-7x28-beware-of-this-person

Or paypal where you can at least dispute the transaction if you have any issues and someone from paypal with review the evidence.  

and if your a seller, just make sure you document the transaction and you shouldn't have any problems with paypal. I never have. the only way you would is if the seller decided to be a dick...

anyways.... I come from the car forum world where Paypal is used without question and usually without issue and involves shipping very expensive items long distances to buyers. ($2k turbos etc..) so I don't understand what the hang up is with all these gun people/gunbroker people.
